<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Chloë Sevigny has been mastering motherhood since welcoming her firstborn back in May with boyfriend Sinisa Mačković. </p>

<p>And the Golden Globe winner has been continuing to turn some major looks during her walks with son Vanja.</p>

<p>She served another playful 19th century look Tuesday in ruffles and pleats, as she took her newborn baby boy for walk with a friend through the East Village neighborhood of New York City.</p>

<p>Antique chic: Chloë Sevigny served another playful 19th century look Tuesday in ruffles and pleats, as she took her newborn baby boy Vanja for walk with a friend through the East Village neighborhood of New York City</p>

<p>The 45-year-old donned a black-and-white houndstooth pinafore with large ruffles down the sides and a pleated mid-length skirt.</p>

<p>She layered the frock over a fitted charcoal short-sleeve top with some chunky black leather ankle boots and matching tube socks.</p>

<p>Chloë finished the look with a white face mask, as she carried a black patent leather handbag, trimmed in white and printed with 'Ciao Bella.'</p>

<p>She was joined by an equally stylish friend, as she walked Vanja in a stroller, before they took a seat on a park bench. </p>

<p>Ruffles and pleats: The 45-year-old donned a black-and-white houndstooth pinafore with large ruffles down the sides and a pleated mid-length skirt</p>

<p>Leather boots: She layered the frock over a fitted charcoal short-sleeve top with some chunky black leather ankle boots and matching tube socks</p>

<p>Ciao bella: Chloë finished the look with a white face mask, as she carried a black patent leather handbag, trimmed in white and printed with 'Ciao Bella'</p>

<p>Friendly outing: She was joined by an equally stylish friend, as she walked Vanja in a stroller, before they took a seat on a park bench</p>

<p>Although the American Psycho actress appeared to be enjoying the outing, she recently admitted to W Magazine that going out these days makes her anxious.</p>

<p>She said: 'I would say that my neuroses around that have really amped up because of the small child and my mother. I guess it’s not even neuroses at this point, it’s just what everybody is doing. It’s common.' </p>

<p>Chloë added: 'I’m walking around a lot, I like to push him around in the stroller, and a lot of people walk by shouting without masks on.</p>

<p>Mama bear: The American Psycho actress recently admitted to W Magazine that going out these days makes her anxious: 'I would say that my neuroses around that have really amped up because of the small child and my mother'</p>

<p>New parents: She's been mastering motherhood since welcoming her firstborn back in May with boyfriend Sinisa Mačković</p>

<p>Secret pregnancy: The veteran 'it' girl revealed that while filming her new series in Italy, she kept her pregnancy a secret from the cast and crew (pictured in March, 2020)</p>

<p>'Like, just put it on! Is it that hard? I know it’s hot and that’s miserable, but bring an extra one so you can change, or don’t shout.'</p>

<p>She also plays a mother in her latest project, the new Luca Guadagnino HBO show We Are Who We Are, which premiered last week.</p>

<p>The veteran 'it' girl revealed that while filming the series in Italy, she kept her pregnancy a secret from the cast and crew.</p>

<p>She explained: 'It was a little awkward. I love going out with the crew and the cast and having drinks, but I was very tired all the time. I wasn’t so sick, but I did have other, hormonal side effects. Navigating that was tricky.'</p>

<p>Leading lady: She also plays a mother in her latest project, the new Luca Guadagnino HBO show We Are Who We Are, which premiered last week</p>
